com.ibm.team.repository.common.query

Interface IDataQuery

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IQuery

    public interface IDataQuery
extends IQuery
    a data query is a type of query used for retrieving fields of related items, or values computed by aggregate or scalar functions. The result of a data query is an IDataQueryPage.
    Since:
    0.5

        static final IQuery.Factory<IDataQuery,IQueryModel> FACTORY
        Global factory instance for clients to create new query instances.

        Example usage:

        TeamQueryModel t = TeamQueryModel.ROOT;
        IDataQuery query = IDataQuery.FACTORY.newInstance(t);
        query.select(t.someAttribute());

      • count

        ISelectionElement count()
        Creates a selection element that represents the count of the aggregate of matching results for the query model ROOT. Note that if an aggregate function is included in a select clause and the query includes an order by or group by clause then the aggregate function expression must be included in the order by/group by clause.
        Returns:
        a new selection element that can be added to the selection list using one of the select methods

      • groupBy

        IQuery groupBy(IField aField)
        Adds the fields to the tuple to be used for grouping data results using aggregate functions (e.g., count()

        Example:
        TeamQueryModel t = TeamQueryModel.ROOT;
        IDataQuery query = IDataQuery.FACTORY.newInstance(t);

        query.groupBy(t.name());

        would return results like:

        Team USA, 25
        Team Canada, 30

        Parameters:
        aField - a model field, acquired by traversing to an attribute from the query model root.
